 electronic substitute for the experience of reading a physical book. The touchscreen interface gives you the feeling of turning actual book pages, while the screen mimics the appearance of paper so your device doesn&#39;t catch the sun if you&#39;re reading outside; there&#39;s nothing like squinting through an irritating glare while reading a book to give you a colossal headache.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/54025-kindle-touch7.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/aucTVUYPffTjMM34rKk5vn.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"aucTVUYPffTjMM34rKk5vn","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/aucTVUYPffTjMM34rKk5vn.jpg","alt":""},"id":"1e991690-6b8f-43f4-802c-5dd28b53e745","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The Kindle Touch incorporates all of the multimedia features found in the Kindle Keyboard, including support for less-common book file formats and compatibility with AA and MP3 files for audiobooks. The Touch also has text-to-speech functionality so that you can set your Kindle up to read a book to you as you nap or prepare dinner.","The Touch also supports the major image file types such as JPG, PNG, GIF and BMP. While the Kindle Touch isn&#39;t much of a substitute for the real thing as far as picture viewing is concerned, it is helpful in that it allows you to keep illustrations from your favorite books (even if they aren&#39;t shown in color)."]},"id":"6f925ac9-0e18-498d-9f4a-6ac9d5866bcc","type":"text"},{"data":{"path":"/6mnrgo2HzXcUPefBdgivMa.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"The Kindle Touch takes eBook reading ease to a whole new level. The interface is simple, based entirely on touch. It will seem extremely familiar to smartphone users since the entire interface seems strikingly similar to a mobile application you&#39;d use on a tablet or a smartphone.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/54025-kindle-touch2.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos